items.name: Concept Nozomi - Shin megami Tensei 4/4A (Character)
items.description:
This is a LORA of the character Nozomi from the ATLUS JRPG Shin Megami Tensei 4 and 4A. Unlike most other models I have made, this was trained on single poorly scanned image of concept art, edited, and enhanced by AI, of a character that had a different final appearance in the official release of the game. Based off of that model, the dataset was then iterated upon multiple times using AI generated data. I dont expect this model to get any attention, but this was just a fun little experiment I wanted to try, and I like the final result a lot.

To prompt this character, enter "<lora:NozomiConcept:0.7>Nozomi, red jacket, red shorts, cape, goggles around neck, blue earrings, black gloves". Additional optional full body tags include "knee pads, thigh straps, pouch, boots".

This LORA was trained on the model AnythingElsev4.5 at Clip Skip 2. I think the results are best with the strength at 0.7 and CFG at 3 ~ 6, using this model specifically.

items.name: Ryuichi Sakamoto
items.description:
If you enjoy my models and want to help support my releases, I always need a coffee!

I've decided to release this to gauge interest in future releases of styles and artists I've been working on. Please don't rip this off as your own, or do anything crazy with it. I am not releasing it for professional or commercial use, this is just for personal use and non-commercial research purposes. Please respect him and his legacy, RIP. And please share your results!

Ryuichi Sakamoto (Japanese: 坂 本 龍 一) (January 17, 1952 – March 28, 2023) was a Japanese composer, record producer, and actor who pursued a diverse range of styles as a solo artist and as a member of Yellow Magic Orchestra (YMO).

None of the YMO members come out correctly in the base model. I've already released Takahashi, and will get around to Hosono eventually.

  • Use "ryuichi sakamoto" as your keyword

  • This LoRA stacks well on almost all models I've tried, from photorealistic to anime

  • Works best between 0.7-1.0

  • Please reference my posted generations for prompts, none have been retouched or inpainted, but I ran them through CN Tile + Tiled Diffusion.

items.name: Avatar Wan Style (from The Legend of Korra) LoRA
items.description:
Avatar Wan style (from The Legend of Korra) LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕


I always liked this part of season 2. This is made with screenshots from episode 7 and 8, which tell the Avatar Wan story. I wasn't sure about this because there are no female characters in that flashback for some reason, and it's 90% Avatar Wan interacting with odd creatures and minor characters. However it seems it turned out good.

Should be used at around 1 weight with AnyLoRA ckpt and with the trigger avatar wan.

Keep in mind this is not a character LoRA, so it can't really reproduce characters from the show, but it can get pretty close with accurate prompting. This is very much intended for you to create your own characters. It should work on basically every model, but it's accurate only on AnyLoRA as far as I've seen, as that one tends to be more "style neutral".


How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Ryu (Street Fighter Series)
items.description:
Hello there!

I was a bit worried cause it was the very first time training an already existant character/concept (I use to draw or 3D model them). Some people requested if I can train some characters from videogames and TV series and well, here we are. I will be doing styles too but wanted to test my self a bit.

It was trained using internet images, some drawings here and there and polishing and fixing as much as possible (ironically I had to take out the two ribbons of the red bandana cause caused conflict).

Models tested: Faetastic, Dreamshaper 3.32 clipfix, GhostMix 1.2, Colorful v3, Rev Animated 1.22...


Token is: sfr1v and strength recommended is 0.8-1.X


This LORA is good at:
***********************
- Anime style output/semi realistic style outputs/concept illustrations of Ryu.
- Any type of portrait, side portrait, half body shot, face shot you can imagine.
- Create surroundings (if prompted, if not black and white background are designed for it)

- Mixing with other LORAs.

This LORA suffers with:
*************************
- Hands. Yup.
- Standing poses where hands are shown (will fuck the art)

So if you want to do some cool poses I'd extremely recommend to use ControlNet.


How to Prompt
******************
- Portrait/side portrait/half body shot/etc., sfr1v, environment, etc.
- If you use negative embedding CAUTION. This LORA was trained under specific exp. settings so you may need to drop bellow 0.7 or don't use token in the prompt.
- You can always invoke ryu with short black hair, red bandana/head band, white outfit/karate outfit even without using the token. This is specially useful to make advanced combinations in the prompting.

IMPORTANT!

I wrote an article here and it's like my finetunning diary for the ones interested with releases upcoming, trainings done, exclusive patreon models previews, personal thoughts, etc. So if you want to see what I'm planning or what I'm into, feel free to take a look.

That's all! Enjoy and feel free to support me in the Patreon


Thanks!

A fairly standard cute anime style, but with exceptionally sharp image quality and unusually good hands. This might serve as a good basis for other Lyco mixes.
